label chapter6:

    # [Scene: Rooftop Sanctuary | Damp Morning]

    scene bg ch6_4001e7_1 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Gentle piano, rising warmth]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Soft water drip, distant gulls, a low murmur of neighbors setting up tools]
    "You climb the narrow wooden ramp before the sun fully trusts the morning. The air is humid and bright with the metallic sweetness of salt; it smells like the town's memory and the possibility you keep"
    "trying to build. Your boots slap softly on the deck; every step makes the planks sigh. Around you, neighbors squat in borrowed gloves, cupping soil like something holy."
    show elias_novak at left:
        zoom 0.7

    elias_novak "You're late, and the basil is judging you."
    "he teases, but his hands are full of seedlings"
    show maya_serrano at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_serrano "Guilty as charged."
    "you laugh; your braid swings, a small pendulum against the collarbone that never fails to steady you"
    "You plant with method: fingers pressing roots into raised beds, the habit of a coordinator translating into careful spacing, into the patience of systems. Finn ducks under a pulley you asked him to rig, his palms"
    "showing the white of old calluses. He passes you a rope and your fingers meet his — brief, familiar warmth."
    show finn_serrano at center:
        zoom 0.7

    finn_serrano "You want the north bed for the greens. Rosa left a note."
    "he grins, and there's a softness to the way he speaks about the town, as if it's both problem and prayer"

    maya_serrano "Perfect. We're going vertical there — more yield per square, less strain on the soil."
    "The solar fabric above hums faintly; it keeps shade and catches light in a way that feels like compromise made into something beautiful. Each raised bed is a small argument against what the sea has taken. Each seed is a sentence: we will try."

    menu:
        "Whistle an old fishing song while you work":
            "You clear your throat and a thin, off-key line of melody starts. A few heads lift; someone joins. The melody stitches people into a loop of shared, practical hope."
        "Hush, focus on the work":
            "You keep your mouth shut and your hands moving. Conversation picks up around you — plans, measurements, jokes — and the silence becomes a quiet kind of resolve."

    # --- merge ---
    "Dr. Hana arrives with the neat, impatient gait of someone who has spent her life translating oceans into equations. Her tablet blooms with models the way a blossom opens to light. She sets it on the"
    "makeshift table, and neighbors inch closer, curiosity and the need for guidance in their faces."
    hide elias_novak
    show dr_hana_park at left:
        zoom 0.7

    dr_hana_park "We can show them how the modules attach. If we use the recycled pallet framework and the lattice bonding, maintenance stays local."
    "she taps the screen, drawing a simple animation"

    maya_serrano "And it scales? If they like it you can replicate it, tile by tile?"

    dr_hana_park "Exactly. The data shows a significant reduction in immediate surge impact for the neighborhood banded with these barriers — not a magic cure, but an actionable reduction. And you all are already doing the hardest part: sustaining it."
    "Her voice is both laboratory and lighthouse. You feel the red thread at your wrist buzz with old promises; this time, promise has a blueprint to rest on. Hope isn't naive here — it's documented, traceable, modular."
    # [Scene: Rosa’s Café | Midday]
    hide maya_serrano
    hide finn_serrano
    hide dr_hana_park

    scene bg ch6_4001e7_2 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Espresso machine, low conversation, the clack of cups]
    "Rosa's café smells like roast and sugar and the kind of comfort that waits for weary organizers. The community maps are pinned across a table: ink lines, thumbtacks, smudged hand-drawn arrows that show supply routes, shelter points, and where the modular barriers would attach to existing jetties."
    show rosa_alvarez at left:
        zoom 0.7

    rosa_alvarez "If the council is looking for a low-cost demonstration, you give them numbers and a crowd that shows up every Saturday, and they have to notice."
    "she says, handing you a biscotti like a benediction"
    show maya_serrano at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_serrano "We have the Saturdays. We have the people."
    "you tap a dot on the map — a cluster of homes that have already offered to host a prototype module"

    rosa_alvarez "Then we can make them see the value — not just in engineering, but in the fact that these are people's lives."
    "You read faces in the room: tired, skeptical, glinting with a new calculation. The arrests and the broken headlines are still a raw edge, but what you are building now is quieter, cumulative."

    menu:
        "Lead with the human stories in the presentation":
            "You put forward the faces behind the data. You tell the council about the mother with two jobs and the shopkeeper who won't leave his mural. Eyes soften; people in the room nod, remembering why this matters."
        "Lead with the modular data and cost comparisons":
            "You lay out the numbers Hana modeled. The room leans in. Skeptical eyebrows lower as pragmatic minds meet practical plans. Confidence ripples through the group."

    # --- merge ---

    "Dr. Hana Park: (softly, to you) "Both — your stories make the grant committee empathize, the models make them fund. We bridge the emotional and the technical." / Maya Serrano" "Then we do both."

    "Dr. Hana Park (softly, to you)" "Both — your stories make the grant committee empathize, the models make them fund. We bridge the emotional and the technical."

    maya_serrano "Then we do both."
    "your voice feels steady; the plan feels like a tide turning"
    # [Scene: Harbor (Kestrel Marine Development Office Across the Harbor) | Early Afternoon]
    hide rosa_alvarez
    hide maya_serrano

    scene bg ch6_4001e7_3 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Low brass, hopeful undertow]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Distant horns, the soft clink of construction far away]
    "Across the water, Noah Kestrel watches — not with the hunger of a takeover but with the measured attention of someone weighing risk and duty. When he reaches out, it's through a proposal that is careful, framed in terms of assistance rather than acquisition."
    show noah_kestrel at left:
        zoom 0.7

    noah_kestrel "Your demonstration shows a replicable approach. My team can help with engineering tolerances and anchoring systems."
    "he offers the tablet; the contract is not there — only plans and a handshake in principle"
    show maya_serrano at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_serrano "We need technical capacity, and you need assurance we won't be sidelined."

    noah_kestrel "Then we make a memorandum of understanding: community oversight on deployment, local training programs, shared maintenance. You keep control; we provide stabilization expertise."
    "The exchange is cautious, careful. Noah's voice is a steady keel. You sense the corporate machine behind him, but also the small human ledger inside — a man who, by his own history, can see what neglect does. He does not offer to buy the town. He offers scaffolding."

    noah_kestrel "I grew up with floodlines on maps. If these modules succeed, we can adapt the blueprints for other towns. You get technical refinements without ceding community governance."

    maya_serrano "We accept help that respects our autonomy. We won't hand this over."

    noah_kestrel "Agreed."
    "his answer is clipped but sincere; you can see it twitch at the corners of his eyes when he looks at the model — a private relief"
    "Outside, Mayor Lillian Cho reads your group's report on camera; her face — always practiced — loosens in the soft light. She announces a conditional municipal grant at a press gathering: funding for a pilot if"
    "the proposal meets safety and inclusivity parameters. Her words are careful, but they lean toward partnership instead of paternalism."
    show mayor_lillian_cho at center:
        zoom 0.7

    mayor_lillian_cho "We are prepared to allocate a conditional grant to community-led modular defenses, contingent on safety reviews and community oversight. Saltbridge belongs to its people."
    "The statement is small, bureaucratic, and enormous. The town's radio crackles with the headline. Someone in a nearby boat whoops. You stand frozen for one heartbeat, then the world tilts — not to triumph, not yet — but to the steady work of recovery."
    # [Scene: Rooftop Sanctuary | Night — Plan-Checking]
    hide noah_kestrel
    hide maya_serrano
    hide mayor_lillian_cho

    scene bg ch6_4001e7_4 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Warm strings, intimate]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Pages rustle, a kettle somewhere; your laughter muffled by fabric]
    "Night folds itself around you. Plan-checking becomes ritual: a shared map, margins crowded with annotations, a pen passed back and forth like a baton. Elias leans in to trace a line, and a strand of hair falls into his eyes. You push it back without thinking, fingers brushing his temple."
    show elias_novak at left:
        zoom 0.7

    elias_novak "I keep thinking about the first time we tried to put sandbags in front of Mrs. Ortega's house. We were clumsy and cold and tired, but she brought lemon bars and told us we were doing sacred work."
    show maya_serrano at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_serrano "She called it 'organized stubbornness.' I thought that worked as a slogan."

    elias_novak "You do so much, Maya. I worry you'll carry everyone on your back."
    "he chuckles; then his face grows quiet"

    maya_serrano "And you think I should run? I need to be the one who keeps the map."

    elias_novak "No. I think —"
    "he searches for words"
    "'— I think you deserve people who can carry the map with you. Not to take it away.'"
    "There's a pause where plans and hearts both re-draw themselves. Your braid knocks at your collarbone; Elias's fingers tap a steady rhythm on the blueprint. In this small luminous moment, repair is not only civic but human."

    maya_serrano "I didn't know how to let anyone help before. The arrests made me think I had to be... impermeable."

    elias_novak "Impermeable doesn't sound like you. It sounds lonely."

    maya_serrano "Better than useless."

    elias_novak "You're not useless. You make people do better work."
    "He meets your eyes and the space between you fills, not with escape from the problem, but with a shared weight made lighter by both hands. The plan in front of you is a thing of"
    "cardboard and ink; the plan between you is a promise: you won't shoulder this burden alone."

    menu:
        "Trace your finger along the projection and whisper a practical correction":
            "You point out a vulnerability at the north joint and suggest a small reinforcement. Elias nods, impressed by your detail. He records it carefully, then presses his forehead to yours in a brief, grateful contact."
        "Close the blueprint and say instead, 'Come with me to the boardwalk'":
            "You fold the papers away and tug Elias toward the door. He grins, surprised, and follows. The night air hits you both, salt and possibility, and the conversation softens into easy laughter as you walk."

    # --- merge ---
    "Saltbridge Boardwalk | Dawn"
    # [Scene: Saltbridge Boardwalk | Dawn]
    hide elias_novak
    hide maya_serrano

    scene bg ch6_4001e7_5 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Full orchestra swell — hopeful, steady]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Tools clanking in rhythm, children calling, seagulls less mournful today]
    "Dawn feels like a clean page. The pilot modules click into place like good sentences finishing themselves, and neighbors who once argued across fences now pass tools and tea. Finn checks a knot and gives a"
    "thumbs-up; Rosa hands out steaming cups with flour on her apron and pride in her eyes. Dr. Hana watches measurements with a small, private smile. Noah consults from a clipboard, offering a precise adjustment and then"
    "stepping back."

    "Mayor Lillian Cho (addressing the gathered crowd)" "This is what I hoped for when I took this job: people who know their town and are ready to act. We will monitor, fund training, and, most importantly, listen."
    "You stand halfway between the rooftop and the sea, your compass warm against your sternum, the red thread on your wrist knotted where new hands have tied it — an emblem not of isolation but of"
    "woven support. The grant rolls through, the modules hold through a strong tide, and the Rooftop Sanctuary expands into a network of green, humming roofs across Saltbridge."

    "Elias Novak (quiet, near you)" "Look at that. You did it."
    show maya_serrano at left:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_serrano "We did it."
    "you let your gaze trace the line of people working — colleagues, friends, neighbors"
    "It's not perfect. There are houses still on the line, and policies still grinding slow. There will be storms and hard decisions. But for the first time in a long while, the horizon doesn't feel like a verdict. It feels like a future you can shape."

    "Rosa Alvarez (handing you a mug)" "You look like someone who slept three hours but finally finished a sentence."

    maya_serrano "That's probably accurate."
    "The town is not saved in one act. It's saved in mornings like this: neighbors trading shelter for seedlings, engineers translating hope into tolerances, a mayor who listens, a corporate hand that learns to work beside"
    "rather than over. Love — yours with Elias — isn't an escape route from responsibility; it's a connective force that binds repair to care."

    "Elias Novak (taking your hand in the light)" "Stay with me in all this. Not because I need help, but because I want to be there."

    maya_serrano "I will."
    "your voice is steady, the compass in your palm cold and alive"
    "You walk the boardwalk with your hands full of plans and your pockets full of small commitments. Saltbridge will continue to change; you will continue to make choices you will sometimes regret and sometimes celebrate. Tonight's"
    "work tastes like coffee and salt and the plain, stubborn joy of building something that resists being taken away."
    hide maya_serrano

    scene bg ch6_4001e7_6 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Resolving chord, bright but grounded]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: The tide, patient and less menacing than before]
    "You feel the red thread at your wrist — not a noose, but a lifeline knotted into the hands around you. You think of the neighbor you lost and of the many who woke today to"
    "something worth fighting for with a different kind of fury: the daily work of repair. Your compass rests flat against your chest; when you breathe, it moves with you."
    "You had meant 'everything.' You had not meant 'alone.' This morning proves the promise doesn't require that. It requires presence — steadiness, stubbornness, shared labor, and the courage to start again each day."

    scene bg ch6_4001e7_7 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Fade into a single, hopeful piano motif]

    scene bg ch6_4001e7_8 at full_bg
    "THE END"
    # [GAME END]
    return
